📌 Project Objective

Design and implement a secure, cost-optimized AWS DataSync architecture to transfer ~1000 GB/month of WAS server log files from source servers to Amazon S3 for archival, with lifecycle-based storage tiering.

The system must:

Support scheduled daily transfers

Use least-privilege IAM

Encrypt data in transit and at rest

Include monitoring and alerting

Be production-ready and scalable

Follow AWS Well-Architected Framework (Security + Cost Optimization pillars)

🔷 Architecture Requirements
Source Environment

WAS servers storing logs under:

/logs/

Logs rotated daily

Approx 42GB/day generation

Source may be:

EC2-based WAS servers

OR on-premises WAS servers

Design solution to support both.

🔷 AWS Services to Use

AWS DataSync

Amazon S3

AWS IAM

AWS KMS

Amazon CloudWatch

Amazon SNS (optional alerting)

AWS Organizations (if multi-account)

